{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HbBjXcdB8HFm1jCZw4bzTX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I can see the issue now. The configmap `es-transport-ca-bundle` only has `ca1.crt` in it. The precondition created two CA secrets (`es-transport-ca1` and `es-transport-ca2`), but the bundle only contains ca1. The cluster may need both CA certificates in the bundle to be trusted by all nodes.\n\nLet me understand the scenario better. The case is `transport-additional-ca-trust`. The precondition:\n1. Created es-transport-ca1 (self-signed)\n2. Created es-transport-ca2 (self-signed)\n3. Put only ca1 into the es-transport-ca-bundle\n\nBut the current state shows the cluster is green with 3 nodes running, which contradicts the precondition saying it should be degraded. Let me look more closely at the StatefulSet configuration—maybe some nodes are signed by ca2 and can't join the cluster because ca2 isn't in the trusted bundle.\n\nActually, the precondition deleted a pod that doesn't exist, so that was ineffective. Looking at the pod ages, they all restarted recently even though the StatefulSet is 40 minutes old, suggesting the precondition triggered a rolling restart. The cluster is now green, so I need to check the case definition to understand what the expected outcome should be.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3375,"cache_read_input_tokens":33251,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3375},"output_tokens":31,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"063321c4-c6bb-49a8-a24d-2e7504be3e04","uuid":"0a58354e-a155-453c-8ae3-6f0fe405cea2","request_id":"req_011Ccewg91BikQEVG7KA8KRa"}
