{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CKo3kAWBDRT1rrQGv8CHXU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the scenario completely:\n\n1. The precondition created two CAs: `es-transport-ca1` and `es-transport-ca2`\n2. It put ONLY `ca1.crt` in the `es-transport-ca-bundle` configmap\n3. The StatefulSet's transport layer uses this bundle for peer trust\n4. Pods 0 and 1 use certificates signed by CA1 (trusted)\n5. Pod 2 uses a certificate signed by CA2 (NOT trusted because ca2 is not in the bundle)\n6. This should mean pod 2 can't join the cluster, yet the health check showed 3 nodes, which contradicts that expectation\n\nLet me look back at what the precondition actually did—it created the CA secrets without the node certificates, then configured the bundle with only ca1, and attempted to delete the pod.\n\nThe precondition ran as a probe that passed, suggesting the faulted state was already in place. This tells me the full cluster setup happened in an earlier stage with proper certificates, and `transport_ca_fault_replant` only modified the configmap to include just one CA. Now I need to check how the StatefulSet uses that CA bundle to understand why the cluster is reporting 3 nodes. If the probe passes, it skips the apply step since the fault is already planted, but if it fails, the apply runs to re-plant it. Looking at the precondition logs, the apply did run—creating the transport CA secrets and bundle configmap with only the CA certificate—which means the probe failed and the fault was re-planted. Now I'm trying to figure out why the cluster is still showing 3 nodes when the pod should have bounced.\n\nThe precondition only updated the configmap with the ca1-only bundle, but the pods were already running with their transport certificates from earlier. Kubernetes automatically updates configmaps mounted as volumes, but Elasticsearch needs to either watch for changes or restart to pick them up. Since all three pods restarted recently and the cluster is showing 3 nodes in green, it seems the pods may have already established connections before the configmap change took effect.\n\nWait, I need to look more carefully at what the precondition actually created. The `es_env_ready` path ran first and created complete secrets with ca.crt, node.crt, and node.key, but then `transport_ca_fault_replant` only created secrets with just the ca.crt file. The StatefulSet needs those full transport certificates to start properly, so I should check what the StatefulSet is actually mounting.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8719,"cache_read_input_tokens":37609,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8719},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"063321c4-c6bb-49a8-a24d-2e7504be3e04","uuid":"ad90bac4-2f30-4207-9678-dd58758b17d7","request_id":"req_011CcewhZvfK2r6AZFmw377j"}
