{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_013mqhfpyPDPfpP85ZCKSjnL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The fix is complete. The `es-transport-ca-bundle` configmap now contains both CA1 and CA2 certificates (verified: 2 `BEGIN CERTIFICATE` markers), and the Elasticsearch cluster is healthy with 3 nodes in `green` status.\n\n**Root cause:** The precondition (`transport_ca_fault_replant`) had re-planted a fault where the transport CA bundle only contained CA1's certificate. Pod `es-cluster-2` is signed by CA2, so without CA2 in the trust bundle, it cannot be trusted by peers on the transport layer.\n\n**Fix:** Extracted the CA2 certificate from the `es-transport-ca2` secret and appended it to the `es-transport-ca-bundle` configmap alongside CA1, giving all nodes mutual trust."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":455,"cache_read_input_tokens":54533,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":455},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"063321c4-c6bb-49a8-a24d-2e7504be3e04","uuid":"564fcc5b-08ee-4f9f-8b46-1a109e061d91","request_id":"req_011CcewpfF62E8yJBP46nFRP"}
